A8: (for i,j being Nat holds ([ i,j ] in ( Indices ( CCirc p ) ) implies ( ( CCirc ( - p ) ) * (i,j) ) = ( - ( ( CCirc p ) * (i,j) ) )))
proof
let i being Nat;
let j being Nat;
assume A9: [ i,j ] in ( Indices ( CCirc p ) );
then A10: ( ( ( i - j ) mod n ) + 1 ) in ( Seg n ) by A2,CKB3:1;
( ( CCirc ( - p ) ) * (i,j) ) = ( ( - p ) . ( ( ( i - j ) mod ( len ( - p ) ) ) + 1 ) ) by A5,A7,A9,CKB9:def 1
.= ( ( comp K ) . ( p . ( ( ( i - j ) mod ( len p ) ) + 1 ) ) ) by A6,A1,A10,FUNCT_1:13
.= ( ( comp K ) . ( ( CCirc p ) * (i,j) ) ) by A4,A9,CKB9:def 1
.= ( - ( ( CCirc p ) * (i,j) ) ) by VECTSP_1:def 13;
hence thesis;
end;
